<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/933421-is-wolfe-easier-to-read-than-faulkner">Is Wolfe easier to read than Faulkner?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_933421'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F12448.Look_Homeward_Angel">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/933421-is-wolfe-easier-to-read-than-faulkner">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/933421-is-wolfe-easier-to-read-than-faulkner">See all 6 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/24281047-kelsey-hess"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1581877034i/24281047._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/24281047-kelsey-hess">Kelsey Hess</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Wolfe is easier to read for me as he uses sufficient punctuation. Both are gifted writers. It&apos;s like this: if you hold your breath through one of Faul<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Wolfe is easier to read for me as he uses sufficient punctuation. Both are gifted writers. It's like this: if you hold your breath through one of Faulkner's massive sentences, you'll likely asphyxiate.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

